  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: If something goes wrong (not enough funds to cover amount +fee, network error, etc) after user provided valid password and tap on Sign Transaction we need to show the feedback about it. For example, a popup with error and stack trace or we re-use Transaction Sent screen and put their some other text instead of `Transaction is sent`. Such error handling should be on Sign Transaction screen if user\r\n- sends funds from Wallet via Send\r\n- sends tx from Unsigned \r\n- sends tx from chat\r\n\r\nCurrently (wrong behaviour): After user taps on Sign Transaction loading indicator is shown for a while and that's it. So, user stays on the same screen with same password request and does not know what happened.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nhttps://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/6833063/sessions/8/?accessToken=ayids-dPjUKPoS-OQrSAPOV-iwk\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- Send all funds you have (it's not handled now as a separate error) or as another error state: switch off wifi to get offline mode and type valid amount you have\r\n- Type password and tap on Sign Transaction\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOs 10.3.1, Galaxy S6 Android 6.0.1",
